Wait for the e-photo to be validated

Here’s where to do it step-by-step in France:

Go to ANTS official site
https://permisdeconduire.ants.gouv.fr

Log in

Use FranceConnect (your tax account, Ameli, La Poste ID, etc.).

Start the request

In the dashboard: choose “Perte du permis de conduire” (lost licence).

The system will open a new application and generate the provisional attestation (the RIR you already have).

Upload documents (the step you’re asking about):

E-photo + signature code: from an ANTS-certified photo booth, photographer, or smartphone app (Smartphone iD, etc.). You’ll only type in the 22-character code, not upload the file yourself.

Pièce d’identité: scan/photo of passport or CNI.

Justificatif de domicile <6 mois: EDF, telecom bill, or rent receipt.

Timbre fiscal 25 €: buy directly online (they give you a code), or upload proof if you already bought one.

Submit

Once validated, you’ll see your dossier appear in your “Mes démarches en cours.”

Statuses progress from En cours d’instruction → En cours de fabrication → Fabrication terminée → Expédié.

You're probably referring to a Google Nest Hub (previously called Google Nest Home or Google Home Hub), and yes—it’s managed via your Google Home app, which was likely installed and configured on your old phone. Here's how to hook it up to your new phone:


---

✅ Steps to Reconnect Your Nest Hub to Your New Phone:

1. Install the Google Home App

On your new phone, download the Google Home app from the Play Store.

Sign in with the same Google account you used on your old phone (important).



2. Connect to the Same Wi-Fi

Make sure your new phone is on the same Wi-Fi network as the Nest Hub.



3. Open the Google Home App

Once signed in and connected to Wi-Fi, open the app.

You should see your Nest Hub listed under your "Home" (it might show as "Living Room Display" or a name you set).



4. Verify Control Works

Tap the Nest Hub in the app to see if you can control it (e.g., change volume or settings).

If it works, you're already reconnected—no need to reset.





---

🔁 If You Can't See the Device or Changed Wi-Fi:

If your Nest Hub isn’t showing up (e.g., if you got a new Wi-Fi network or account):

Factory reset the Nest Hub:

Hold down the volume up and volume down buttons on the back simultaneously for ~10 seconds until you hear it confirm a reset.

Then set it up again from scratch in the Google Home app.




---

Google Cloud & Confluent Opportunity Notes
Account: Intermarché (STIME / Les Mousquetaires)

Opportunity: Drive new Google Cloud Marketplace revenue by migrating and expanding Intermarché's Confluent usage to Confluent Cloud. The goal is to displace competitor Solace and consolidate the client's event-streaming strategy on GCP.

Revenue Potential:

Current Confluent ARR: ~$200K

Potential Growth (Target): ~$300K - $400K

Timeline:

Target for Marketplace Migration: June 2026

New Deal Closure: Unlikely by the end of 2025 due to long sales cycles and the retail peak season.

Key Context:

Intermarché's architecture team is re-evaluating their incumbent solution (Solace), which creates a significant opportunity for Confluent and Google Cloud.

The operations team already uses Confluent and open-source Kafka, but the architecture and leadership teams need to be convinced of the value of a managed cloud service.

The primary decision rests with the CIO on whether to stay with Solace, continue self-managing Kafka, or strategically adopt Confluent Cloud.

Key Next Steps:

Frédéric Carlier (Google): Investigate the ongoing solution evaluation to see if an external consulting firm is involved.

Frédéric Carlier (Google): Engage with Intermarché's leadership to discuss the growth strategy and alignment.

Frédéric Carlier (Google) & Hadi Saboungi (Confluent): Schedule a sync meeting in two weeks to review progress and align on strategy.
